NewsHub uses Redis's vector search capabilities to find contextually similar articles. It creates a vector index with 768-dimensional embeddings stored in RedisJSON documents. The implementation uses cosine similarity for KNN (k-nearest neighbors) searches to find articles with similar semantic content. Here's the key code snippet:

javascript
async findSimilarArticles(articleId, limit = 10) {
  const article = await this.client.json.get(`news:articles:${articleId}`);
  const query = `*=>[KNN $k @embedding $embedding AS score]`;
  const results = await this.client.ft.search('news:vector_index', query, {
    PARAMS: { k: limit, embedding: article.embedding }
  });
  return results.documents.map(doc => ({
    id: doc.id.replace('news:articles:', ''),
    title: doc.value['$.title'],
    similarity: doc.value.score
  });
}

NewsHub uses RedisJSON to store articles as structured documents with full search capabilities. Here's the implementation:

javascript
class RedisService {
  async storeArticle(article) {
    const articleId = `news:articles:${article.id}`;
    await this.client.json.set(articleId, '$', {
      id: article.id,
      title: article.title,
      content: article.content,
      summary: article.summary,
      sentiment: article.sentiment,
      topic: article.topic,
      source: article.source,
      url: article.url,
      publishedAt: article.publishedAt,
      keywords: article.keywords,
      embeddings: article.embeddings
    });
  }
}


This approach allows storing complex hierarchical data while enabling efficient search and retrieval operations through RedisSearch indexes.
